remarks: Proof of ~ ax-11 from the standard axioms of predicate calculus, similar to PM's proof of ~ alcom (PM*11.2).  This proof requires that ` x ` and ` y ` be distinct.  Axiom ~ ax-11 is used in the proof only through ~ nfal , ~ nfsb , ~ sbal , ~ sb8 .  See also ~ ax11-pm .  (Contributed by BJ, 15-Sep-2018.)  (Proof modification is discouraged.)
statement:
ax11-pm2 $p |- ( A. x A. y ph -> A. y A. x ph ) $.
$d x y $.
